Does applying ice really reduce pore size?
Yes… but only for a hot minute. 🧊
When you apply ice to your face, the cold temperature causes your blood vessels to constrict, giving your skin a temporarily tighter, smoother look. Your pores seem smaller—but only until your skin warms up again. Think of it like leaving an ice cube out: it melts. Your pores? They bounce right back to their original size.

So instead of torturing your face with ice cubes every morning, let’s go the science-backed route:
✨ BHA (like salicylic acid): Gets deep into the pores and clears them out.
✨ Niacinamide: Minimizes appearance of pores and improves skin texture.
✨ Retinol: Encourages cell turnover, which helps tighten and refine pores over time.

Real skincare isn’t about quick fixes. It’s about consistency, ingredients that work, and patience.
Your pores deserve more than just a cold shock. 😉
